The stay-at-home directive issued by the Kwara State government to prevent the spread of coronavirus in the state is being abused by some residents, especially youths, commercial vehicle operators and beggars. The partial lockdown of the state is effective only between the early hours of the day and 6 pm. Anything after 6 pm, residents, especially marketers and commercial vehicle operators troop out to ply their trade. The youths have turned virtually every available place within compounds to football fields, without regard for social distancing order. At popular Oja- Oba, near Ilorin Central Mosque and Gambari area, regarded as beggars’ colony, beggars are found in large numbers, begging for alms. They are always there from morning till dusk.  